#1 Treatment recommendation following resection of a node-positive colon adenocarcinoma
We discussed the characteristics of the cancer, including type of malignancy, size, grade, lymph node status.  We discussed the stage of the cancer and that the oncologist today would attempt to quantify the potential risk of cancer recurrence.  I will staff this with Dr. Greg Ruiz through the Oncology GI Clinic, who will outline his recommendations in his subsequent note.
I did review with Mr. Smith typical treatment schedules for aggressive chemotherapy treatment, not so aggressive therapy versus observation.  For treatment recommendations, please refer to Dr. Mendenhall subsequent supervisory note.
ADVANCE DIRECTIVES
Advance directive or living will: Yes, on file at CDSSRBH.
PATIENT EDUCATION
Ready to learn, no apparent learning barriers were identified; learning preferences include listening.  Explained diagnosis and treatment plan; patient expressed understanding of the content.
ADDITION
I have contacted Mr. Smith's primary-care provider, Dr. Pray, to inform her that his creatinine is elevated at 2.4.  At this time, she has recommended alter his diuretic therapy; informed patient it has been recommended that he take his Lasix (furosemide) only once-daily for the next three days; recommend having a repeat blood test done Thursday, and Dr. Pray will follow-up with the patient.  These tests have been ordered.  Patient stated full understanding with this plan.

